A motorist sustained serious injuries after his vehicle crashed into a pillar in South Coast Road in Mobeni, recently. PT Alarms Tactical Unit and PT Ambulance personnel rushed to the scene of the motor vehicle accident where the driver of the Toyota Corolla believed to be in his 30s, allegedly lost control of the vehicle and slammed into a concrete pillar. Spokesperson for PT Alarms, Dhevan Govindasamy, said, “The vehicle somersaulted and landed on its roof.  PT Tactical Unit assisted at the accident scene.” He added, “The driver sustained facial and head injuries. He was carefully extricated from the vehicle by the PT members before the arrival of paramedics. “Metro, Ethekwini Fire department and medical services responded swiftly and the man was stabilised before being transported to the hospital for further treatment.”